Done. Both files have your real Firebase credentials. Upload `upload-ready/portal.html` to your live site and it's fully wired.

One thing to do first in Firebase console: go to **Realtime Database → Rules** and make sure they're set to test mode (read/write open) so the portal can actually save data. It should already be open since you just created it, but worth confirming you see:

```json
{
  "rules": {
    ".read": true,
    ".write": true
  }
}
```

Once that's confirmed and the file is uploaded — client rates stars, assigns looks, writes notes → it all goes to Firebase instantly. You log in as Admin from anywhere, hit **Sync**, and see exactly what they did.

